# 7. 息を合わせて

Honami: Thank you all for sitting down. Now, let's get into the story.
Nene: It's titled “The Star-Chasing Dog”. And it's about...
Children: Hey, let's play a word game.
Children: No, we should thumb wrestle!
Honami: Oh...
Nene: They really can't stay still...
Honami: *Nod* I wish there were some way for us to get them to focus on the stage...
Honami: Oh, Kusanagi, what if we...?!
Nene: Yeah, okay. Let's give it a try.
Association Executive B: Settle down, children! What happened to the zippers on our mouths?
Children: Hey, did you watch that anime?
Children: Yeah, it was awesome!!
Honami: Wait, did you hear something just now?
Children: Huh?
Nene: Yeah, I heard it!
Nene: What was that? It sounded like a dog... Can you guys hear it?
Children: A doggy?
Children: I'm not hearing anything...
Honami: That's strange. I could've sworn I heard one just now...
Children: What would something like that be doing here?!
Nene: I don't know, but... Oh, there it is again!
Nene: Listen closely, everyone.
Children: Hm?
Honami: (Okay, they're all looking at Kusanagi now.)
Honami: (Now I just need to hit the remote...!)
Dog's Voice: <Woof! Woof!>
Children: Oh, there it is!
Children: Where's the doggy?!
Dog's Voice: <Woof!>
Children: Huh? Now it's coming from over there!
Honami: Can you all see where the doggy is?
Children: No. I can hear it, but I can't see it...
Dog's Voice: *Howl*
Nene: Oh, there it is again. But where could it be...?
Children: Hey! Look at the screen...!
Nene: Huh? Where? Hmm... I'm still not seeing it...
Children: Look behind you!
Children: Behind you!
Nene: Behind me?
Children: There!
Honami: Oh, the doggy's tail is making a shadow on the screen!
Nene: Hey, you're right! What's it doing here?
Honami: What if...? Was he so excited that he decided to jump out of the book?
Nene: Maybe.
Nene: We're really sorry! It'll be your turn soon, so just bear with us for a bit longer, okay?
Dog's Voice: <Woof!>
Children: No, the doggy went away...
Honami: Don't worry. He's waiting very patiently for us in this book.
Children: In that book?
Honami: Yes. It's a story about a very kind dog with a very fluffy tail.
Honami: Don't you all want to see him again?
Children: Yeah!
Nene: Great. Then, can you all listen quietly while we read this story to you?
Children: Okay!
Nene: We've somehow managed...
Honami: Yes. Your acting was so convincing, Kusanagi.
Nene: I wouldn't call what I did just now acting... If anything, your quick thinking is what saved us.
Nene: I never would've thought to use the sound recordings and the shadow trick we prepared to get the kids' attention.
MEIKO: <As with any live performance, it's normal to have a lot of things go through your mind...>
MEIKO: <Chiefly, whether or not all the hard work you put in is going to pay off.>
MEIKO: <But I'm sure you two will do just fine. So, go out there and have as much fun as the children are about to.>
Honami: Somebody told me she was sure we'd do a good job... I think we have her to thank.
